org.mym.plog

Class PLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mym.plog.PLog

  • public final class PLog
extends Object
    Entry of all library public API; you can set configurations and launch log requests using this class with only a static method call.
    Since:
    1.0.0

      • prepare

        public static void prepare(Printer... printers)
        Prepare printers; this method should always be called on application start because you should set your own onIntercept logic using Printer interface. 
             
 PLog.prepare(new DebugPrinter(BuildConfig.DEBUG));
        Note that calling this method will clear all printers set before.
        Parameters:
        printers - printers to print logs; they are parallel from each other.
